possible to raise property or corporate taxes, a pattern now growing in the western states. Taxing the Poor demonstrates how sales taxes intended to replace the missing revenue-taxes that at first glance appear fair-actually punish the poor and exacerbate the very conditions that drove them into poverty in the first place.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aPoorxTaxationxSouthern States. 0aPoorxTaxationxUnited States. 0aPoorxTaxationzSouthern States. 0aPoorxTaxationzUnited States. 0aPovertyxSouthern States. 0aPovertyxUnited StatesxSouthern StatesxUnited States. 0aPovertyzSouthern States. 0aPovertyzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aO'Brien, Rourke, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520948938423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520948938.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles